 to require explanation. When carried out at the level of pure play, such subjective acts of interpretation are wit, and the fourth essay analyzes playfully inflated interpretations of domestic spaces and leisure activities as a discourse of private valuation, articulated against commonsense values.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361615840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503616158423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503616158/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles